President Obama commemorates the 50th anniversary of the Immigration and Nationality Act (INA) and praises the bipartisan effort that led to its enactment. The INA abolished an unfair quota system, prohibited discrimination based on country of origin, and recognized the importance of immigration in reuniting families and attracting skilled workers. The President highlights the economic contributions of immigrants and emphasizes the need for comprehensive immigration reform that aligns with the needs of the 21st century, promotes economic growth, and upholds American ideals.